===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|oracle bone script}}, an {{liushu|ic|nocap=y}}: a hand ({{zh-l|*又}}) holding an object (?) among three or more fires ({{zh-l|*火}}). Meaning and significance uncertain.

Various hypotheses exist: possibly poking at firewood, holding a tool inside flames, lighting fires with a torch, etc.

Later, an {{Han compound|又|辛|炏|t1=hand|t2=tool|t3=fire|ls=ic|nocap=y}}. In the {{w|small seal script}}, the {{lang|zh|辛}} component came to be written {{zh-l|*言}}, giving rise to the modern form.

